{"lemma":"رَهْنُ","slug":"رَهْنُ","root":"ر.ه.ن","root_slug":"ر-ه-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ه-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","prep","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16910","n16915"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%87%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mortgage, to pawn"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"subject to, depending or conditional on, pending, liable to"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mortgage"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16910","headword_ar":"رَهَنَ","root":"rhn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhuwnN","text_ar":"رُهُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, S, Msb, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continued, subsisted, lasted, endured, remained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remained fixed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stationary; it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, permanent, constant, firm, steady, stead fast, stable, fixed, fast, settled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"established."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K, TA.) This is the primary signification. (Mgh, TA. *) ―         -b2-  Hence, (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahana biAlmakaAni","text_ar":"رَهَنَ بِالمَكَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He remained, stayed, dwelt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode, in the place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahana","text_ar":"رَهَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, [but this I think to be a mis take,]) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhuwnN","text_ar":"رُهُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) said of a man, and of a camel, (JK, S, * TA,) and of any beast (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigued, tired, weary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jaded."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba Hat~aY rahana","text_ar":"رَكِبَ حَتَّى رَهَنَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rode until he became lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAhinN","text_ar":"رَاهِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-  As trans., see 4, first signification. ―         -b2-  [Hence,] as a law term,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"putting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"placing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"an article of real property ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to remain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a pledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"security,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making"},{"kind":"text","text":"it"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be such, for a debt that is obligatory"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that will become obligatory."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahanahu Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"رَهَنَهُ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahanahu Einodahu","text_ar":"رَهَنَهُ عِنْدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynapN","text_ar":"رَهِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arhnhu","text_ar":"ارهنهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) all signify the same; (S;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He deposited the thing with him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a pledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be in lieu of that which he had taken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received, from him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he pledged the thing to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahanotu AlmataAEa","text_ar":"رَهَنْتُ المَتَاعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAld~ayoni","text_ar":"بِالدَّيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I restricted the commodity"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"placed it in custody, for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of, the debt;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bAldyn","text_ar":"بالدين"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arhnthu","text_ar":"ارهنتهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. var. thereof, but of rare occurrence, and disallowed by those who are held in esteem: (Msb:) for, properly, they say, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodFA Alv~awoba","text_ar":"زَيْدًا الثَّوْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arohanotu","text_ar":"اَرْهَنْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave to Zeyd the garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth, in order that he should deposit it as a pledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with some one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) 'Abd-Allah Ibn Hemmám Es-Saloolee says, (S,) or Hemmám Ibn-Murrah, (TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"maAlikaA ↓ \n      najawotu wa A^arohanotuhumo \n                      \n                     \n                        falam~aA xa$iytu A^aZaAfiyrahumo"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And when I dreaded their nails, I escaped, and gave them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left with them, as a pledge, Málik"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: thus, says Th, all relate the verse, except As, who says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa A^arohanuhumo mAlkA","text_ar":"وَ اَرْهَنُهُمْ مالكا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaving with them, as a pledge, Málik"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: he likens this phrase to the say ing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qumotu wa A^aSuk~u wajohahu","text_ar":"قُمْتُ وَ اَصُكُّ وَجْهَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and this is a good way of explaining it; for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is that which is a deno tative of state; the meaning being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAk~FA wajohahu","text_ar":"صَاكًّا وَجْهَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [accord. to the former reading, in the opinion of Th,] the poet means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I left Málik remaining with them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"not as a pledge; because [when the leaving a thing as a pledge is meant, in his opinion,] one does not say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arohanotu","text_ar":"اَرْهَنْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", but only"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahanotuhu","text_ar":"رَهَنْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) [See, however, 4.] You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahanahu Eanohu","text_ar":"رَهَنَهُ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to be a pledge in lieu of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a poet, asserted by IJ to be a pagan, says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Airohano baniyka Eanohumu A^arohano baniYo"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Make thou thy sons to be pledges in lieu of them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in that case"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will make my sons to be pledges:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baniY","text_ar":"بَنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baniY~a","text_ar":"بَنِىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahanotuhu lisaAniY","text_ar":"رَهَنْتُهُ لِسَانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made my tongue to be as though it were a pledge to him, to be restrained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be used, for his sake"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"benefit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: in this case one should not say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arohanotuhu","text_ar":"اَرْهَنْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, K;) though one says thus of a garment, or piece of cloth, [&c.,] as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahanotuhu","text_ar":"رَهَنْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","JK"]},{"entry_id":"n16915","headword_ar":"رَهْنٌ","root":"rhn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", originally an inf. n., (Msb,) is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marohuwnN","text_ar":"مَرْهُونٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, Msb;) i. e. (Msb) it signifies ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pledge;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing deposited with a person"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, * K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be in lieu of a thing that has been taken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received, from him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that is deposited as a security for a debt:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rihaAnN","text_ar":"رِهَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"has a similar meaning, but is specially applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that is deposited as a bet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wager,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stake;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is likewise originally an inf. n.: (Er-Rághib, TA:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynapN","text_ar":"رَهِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act of giving as a pledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"], like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$atiymapN","text_ar":"شَتِيمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$atomN","text_ar":"شَتْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being added to give intensiveness to the significa tion: then, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is used as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marohuwnN","text_ar":"مَرْهُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the sense explained above, as will be seen in what follows in this paragraph]; (IAth, TA;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynapN","text_ar":"رَهِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n. like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$atiymapN","text_ar":"شَتِيمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to denote the pass. part. n. [used as a subst. pro perly so termed] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", not as an epithet; (Bd in lxxiv. 41;) [or, in other words,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynapN","text_ar":"رَهِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything by reason of which a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as a debt or the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is restricted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appro priated, to oneself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murotahanapN","text_ar":"مُرْتَهَنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K: [I here follow two copies of the K, in which it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u maA A@Hotubisa bihi $aYo'N farahiynapN wa murotahanapN","text_ar":"كُلُّ مَا ا@حْتُبِسَ بِهِ شَىْءٌ فَرَهِينَةٌ وَ مُرْتَهَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the CK, and in the copy of the K followed in the TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farahiynuhu wa murotahanuhu","text_ar":"فَرَهِينُهُ وَ مُرْتَهَنُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which perverts the meaning, though ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynN","text_ar":"رَهِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murotahanN","text_ar":"مُرْتَهَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be used in the same sense as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynapN","text_ar":"رَهِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muzotahanapN","text_ar":"مُزْتَهَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as will be seen in the course of this paragraph: and in the TA, in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@Hotubisa","text_ar":"ا@حْتُبِسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is put"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yHbs","text_ar":"يحبس"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuHobasu","text_ar":"يُحْبَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": there is, however, this difference between ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynapN","text_ar":"رَهِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murotahanapN","text_ar":"مُرْتَهَنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; that the former properly signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing deposited as a pledge;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing taken,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received, as a pledge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rihaAnN","text_ar":"رِهَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhuwnN","text_ar":"رُهُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhunN","text_ar":"رُهُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, K,) this last said to be a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"by Aboo-' Amr Ibn-El-' Alà, but disap proved by Akh, because a word of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolN","text_ar":"فَعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has not a pl. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEulN","text_ar":"فُعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"except in rare and anomalous instances, though he says that it may be [as it is said to be in the Msb] pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rihaAnN","text_ar":"رِهَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and Fr says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhunN","text_ar":"رُهُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rihaAnN","text_ar":"رِهَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this is denied in the M, because any pl. may not be pluralized except when there is express authority for it and when the case does not admit of any other decision; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhonN","text_ar":"رُهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, is another pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [or rather it is a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhunN","text_ar":"رُهُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and another pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather a quasi-pl. n.] is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynN","text_ar":"رَهِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IJ, K,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabiydN","text_ar":"عَبِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabodN","text_ar":"عَبْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynapN","text_ar":"رَهِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahaAy^inu","text_ar":"رَهَايِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqa Alr~ahonu","text_ar":"غَلِقَ الرَّهْنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimaA fiyhi","text_ar":"بِمَا فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pledge became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has become, per manent as a possession, with what was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is, comprised in it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a prov., applied to him who has fallen into a case from which he cannot hope to escape: it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yagolaqui Alr~ahonu","text_ar":"لَا يَغْلَقُِ الرَّهْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Meyd,) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pledge shall not remain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"let not the pledge remain, in the hand of its receiver when its depositer is able to release it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA","text_ar":"لا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here either negative or prohibitive: you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galiqa Alr~ahonu","text_ar":"غَلِقَ الرَّهْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yagolaqu","text_ar":"يَغْلَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guluwqN","text_ar":"غُلُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"galaqN","text_ar":"غَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pledge remained in the hand of the receiver when the depositor was able to release it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, cited in a copy of the “ Jámi' es-Sagheer: ”) the trad. means that the receiver of the pledge shall not have a right to it when the depositer has not released it within a certain time: for it was a custom in the Time of Ignorance for the receiver to keep possession of the pledge in this case; but El-Islám abolished it. (Meyd, * Nh.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa rahonN bika*aA","text_ar":"هُوَ رَهْنٌ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bk*A","text_ar":"بكذا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynapN","text_ar":"رَهِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pledged for such a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taken"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a pledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynN","text_ar":"رَهِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murotahanN","text_ar":"مُرْتَهَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA rahonN bika*aA","text_ar":"اَنَا رَهْنٌ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynN","text_ar":"رَهِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynapN","text_ar":"رَهِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am taken"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a pledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) And [hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA laka rahonN bika*aA","text_ar":"اَنَا لَكَ رَهْنٌ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynapN","text_ar":"رَهِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am responsible,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a surety, to thee for such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biqayodihi","text_ar":"بِقَيْدِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoluhu rahiynapN","text_ar":"رِجْلُهُ رَهِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His leg,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foot, is a pledge for"},{"kind":"text","text":"the safe-keeping of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his shackle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for if the meaning were"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marohuwnapN","text_ar":"مَرْهُونَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"it would be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynN","text_ar":"رَهِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxaloqu","text_ar":"الخَلْقُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almawoti","text_ar":"المَوْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahaAy^inu","text_ar":"رَهَايِنُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mankind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all created beings, are the pledges of death"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa rahonu","text_ar":"هُوَ رَهْنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadi Almaniy~api","text_ar":"يَدِ المَنِيَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the pledge of the hand of death,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of fate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destiny"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; said of one when he has sought, or courted, death. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadiY laka","text_ar":"يَدِى لَكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My hand is a pledge to thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; by which is meant responsibility, or suretiship. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaborK","text_ar":"قَبْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu larahiynu","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَرَهِينُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is the pledge of a grave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which will render him up on the day of resurrection]. (TA.) It is said in the Kur lxxiv. 41, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u nafosK bimaA kasabato rahiynapN","text_ar":"كُلُّ نَفْسٍ بِمَا كَسَبَتْ رَهِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every soul is a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pledged with God"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for what it shall have wrought;"},{"kind":"text","text":"its works being regarded as a debt, for which it will be either released or held in custody to be punished everlastingly]:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rhynp","text_ar":"رهينة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being an inf. n. like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$atiymapN","text_ar":"شَتِيمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to denote the pass. part. n. [in a manner before mentioned] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahonN","text_ar":"رَهْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for if it were an epithet [i. e. used in the proper sense of a pass. part. n.] the word would be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahiynN","text_ar":"رَهِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Bd.) And in lii. 21 of the same,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u","text_ar":"كُلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@moriy^K bimaA kasaba rahiynN","text_ar":"ا@مْرِيٍ بِمَا كَسَبَ رَهِينٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every man is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pledged"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marohuwnN","text_ar":"مَرْهُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Bd, Jel) with God ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einoda A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"عِنْدَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for what he shall have wrought;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that if he have done good, He will release him; but other wise, He will destroy [or hold in confinement and punish] him; (Bd;) or to be punished for evil, and recompensed for good. (Jel.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEaqiyqatihi","text_ar":"بِعَقِيقَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u gulaAmK rahiynapN","text_ar":"كُلُّ غُلَامٍ رَهِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every boy"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is born"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is a pledge for his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eqyqp","text_ar":"عقيقة"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. for the victim that is to be sacrificed for him when his head is shaven the first time; which is com monly regarded as his ransom from the fire of Hell]: i. e., the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eqyqp","text_ar":"عقيقة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is absolutely necessary for him; wherefore he is likened, when not released from it, to a pledge in the hand of the receiver: El-Khattábee says that the best explanation of it is that of Ahmad Ibn-Hambal; that if the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eqyqp","text_ar":"عقيقة"},{"kind":"text","text":"be not sacrificed for the boy and he die an infant, he will not intercede for his parents. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also what next follows."}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","Mgh","K","TA","IJ","Meyd","IAth","JK"]}]}}